Member Function Documentation

void Finder::backwards_traversal ( int  pos  )  [private]

Implements techniques of backwards traversal. Disassembles bytes in reverse order from pos. Founds the most appropriate chain using special rules (all the variables of target instruction should be defined within that chain).

Parameters:
pos Starting point of the process.
